files.Title: BOOSEcode2.BOOSEform
files.Summary: Main Windows Form for running BOOSE programs.

files.Title: BOOSEcode2.MyArray
files.Summary: Custom array implementation that removes BOOSE size restrictions. Supports both integer and real (double) array types in 1D or 2D configurations. Works with peek and poke operations for array element access.

files.Title: BOOSEcode2.MyBoolean
files.Summary: Custom Boolean variable class that removes BOOSE restrictions. Handles boolean values and logical expressions.

files.Title: BOOSEcode2.MyCall
files.Summary: Custom call command for invoking defined methods. Removes BOOSE restrictions on method calls and argument passing. Syntax: call methodName [arg1, arg2, ...]

files.Title: BOOSEcode2.MyCanvas
files.Summary: A simple canvas used by the BOOSE interpreter. Implements Singleton pattern to ensure only one canvas instance exists. Handles drawing shapes, lines, colours, text, and cursor movement.

files.Title: BOOSEcode2.MyCircle
files.Summary: Replacement circle command that uses our canvas and does not have the BOOSE radius restriction.

files.Title: BOOSEcode2.MyClear
files.Summary: Custom clear command that clears the canvas.

files.Title: BOOSEcode2.MyCommandFactory
files.Summary: Custom command factory that creates custom BOOSE commands. Replaces specific BOOSE commands with custom implementations while allowing other standard BOOSE commands to work normally.

files.Title: BOOSEcode2.MyElse
files.Summary: Custom else command for if-else branching. Marks the transition from if-true block to if-false block. When the if condition is true, execution jumps over the else block.

files.Title: BOOSEcode2.MyEnd
files.Summary: Custom end command that closes if, while, for, and method blocks. Removes BOOSE nesting and complexity restrictions. Handles loop continuation and method returns.

files.Title: BOOSEcode2.MyEvaluation
files.Summary: Custom evaluation class for handling standalone variable assignments. Allows assignments like "width = 2*radius" after variable declaration.

files.Title: BOOSEcode2.MyFor
files.Summary: Custom for loop implementation that removes BOOSE iteration restrictions. Supports: for variable = start to end [step increment] Default step is 1 if not specified.

files.Title: BOOSEcode2.MyIf
files.Summary: Custom If command that removes nesting restrictions. Evaluates a boolean condition and executes commands conditionally.

files.Title: BOOSEcode2.MyInt
files.Summary: Custom integer variable implementation that removes BOOSE restrictions. Supports unlimited variable names and no count limits. Handles both declaration and initialization syntax.

files.Title: BOOSEcode2.MyMethod
files.Summary: Custom method command for defining reusable procedures. Removes BOOSE restrictions on method complexity and parameter count. Syntax: method returnType methodName [paramType paramName, ...]

files.Title: BOOSEcode2.MyMoveTo
files.Summary: Custom moveto command that simply forwards to our canvas.

files.Title: BOOSEcode2.MyParser
files.Summary: Custom parser that extends BOOSE's Parser to handle custom variable types. Intercepts int and real declarations to use custom classes, and handles standalone variable assignments.

files.Title: BOOSEcode2.MyPeek
files.Summary: Custom peek command for reading values from array elements. Inherits from MyArray to access array operations. Syntax: peek variable = arrayName row col (2D) or peek variable = arrayName row (1D)

files.Title: BOOSEcode2.MyPoke
files.Summary: Custom poke command for writing values into array elements. Inherits from MyArray to access array operations. Syntax: poke arrayName row col = value (2D) or poke arrayName row = value (1D)

files.Title: BOOSEcode2.MyReal
files.Summary: Custom real number variable implementation that removes BOOSE restrictions. Supports floating-point arithmetic and unlimited variable declarations. Handles variable substitution and expression evaluation.

files.Title: BOOSEcode2.MyRect
files.Summary: Custom rectangle command that draws a rectangle using the application's canvas instead of BOOSE's default one.

files.Title: BOOSEcode2.MyTri
files.Summary: Replacement triangle command that uses our canvas and does not have the BOOSE restrictions.

files.Title: BOOSEcode2.MyWhile
files.Summary: Custom While loop implementation that removes BOOSE restrictions. Executes a block of commands repeatedly while a condition remains true. Syntax: while [condition] ... endwhile

files.Title: BOOSEcode2.MyWrite
files.Summary: Custom write command for displaying text and variable values on the canvas. Supports variable substitution and expression evaluation for int, real, and boolean types.
